caption: The food in this place is good but some recommendations would be: 1. Serve more fries. 2. Don't use frozen lamb. 3. Lower the prices or have better interior decor.

Food was great, service was fabulous! We went for the first time last week on a whim. We were the only people there, came pretty late, and we got stellar service. Melinda was a great server. We will definitely be coming back! I wish they were open for lunch so we could come more!! We got the samosas,  chicken tikka masala and the Athenian Chicken with Naan and Rice. All of it was soooo good! 😀
Great service,  great food.
Amazing food and service! The chicken tikka masala never disappoints!
This place is amazing the food was phenomenal and Melinda our server was so knowledgable and helpful will definitely return.. Go Niners
The biriani was so bad and expensive it was boiled colored rice I wish I could give zero stars terrible food then I ordered vegetable soup that just had a mixture of hot spices🤨going to bed hungry
Please don’t serve fake Indian food. The food is costly too. I never ever saw the price as high as $19.99 for chicken biryani.

If your thinking of coming here for Indian food don't bother. You can get way better Indian cuisine at one of the other Indian restaurants in town for half the price. The menu is very limited. I ended up having vegetable biryani and was so disappointed. A plate of strangely seasoned rice with a few veggies for $19.99. No thanks. I will not be returning.
Great place to eat and drink and the staff/owner are great people!
Absolutely amazing southern Indian style dishes! Haven't had a single thing that I didn't love. Sauces and desserts are made fresh daily. You have to try the chicken 65 and wings both India Hot!
My fifth visit. Everything that I have tried has been outstanding!!!

Vinny’s may be the best Indian/Greek fusion restaurant in Huntsville... purely by accident. I visited on a sleepy Tuesday evening and our group had the run of the place. I was lured in by my love for both Greek and Indian food. This sounds like a place for me.  We ordered a few drinks and appetizers. The first sign that something was amiss was the unannounced substitution of an order of hummus with an order of samosas. Not really a similar item. The chili chicken and spicy wings were tasty.  Upon selecting entrees, I was informed that the “lamb gyros” indeed came from a prepackaged container (think bacon). Hard pass. I ordered lamb kabobs and was informed they do not have any kabobs tonight. That pretty well eliminates half the Greek menu. I ordered a “traditional Greek salad” and the Chicken Tikka Marsala. I figure those two things naturally go together.  The salad contained 3 olives, maybe 2 small pieces of feta, and iceberg lettuce. Not quite on target. The Tikka was okay, but nothing to write home about. The prepackaged Indian at Costco is better (sadly)... or maybe it’s the same??!!??  The kicker is that we were served “naan”.  A pile of prepackaged pita with garlic salt is what showed up. To top it all off, three people ordered Biryani, a traditional dish. It showed up with a side of “raita”... very thick yogurt raita. Looks like tzatziki to me. When asked, we were told, “it’s the same thing.” The person at my table born in India would strongly disagree.  I wanted to give this place 3 stars, but the others who suffered through this disaster of a meal complained for days. Sadly, I can not recommend anything on the menu.

I was passing through Huntsville downtown and accidentally landed at this place..hands down best host/cook who suggested best indian and greek appetizers and entrees. I have tasted at many resturants between St Louis to Atlanta and this places stands out a new level..
Best Indian Taste food in AL.

WOW I've been wanting to go here for so long and Vinny's did not disappoint. Solid prices on lunch specials, delicious Chicken Tikka Masala and Naan. The service was fantastic and she was very kind and personable. This place is great and I hope it gets plenty of love from more Huntsvillians!

I had been craving some good authentic Indian food and Vinny’s did not disappoint. Delicious food, incredibly friendly wait staff, beautiful decor and ambience. I can’t wait to go back and try some other menu items. Just ate there last night and I’m craving more already. Also, perfect date night spot.

Went for lunch and sat quickly.  I had the lamb gyro and my wife had the Chicken tikka masala. One lady taking drink and food orders for 15 people already seated.  We noticed at least 10 people come in and then leave due to waiting for the one server to seat them.  Lamb was pre packed and not on a mechanical skewer.  Chicken was very dry.  All in all, less than average Indian and Greek fusion food.  One server for lunch rush.. lights had a piece of blue painter's tape on each one to make the room seem blue.. weird!  2 stars.
Everything we ate was delicious. Started with a spicy cashews, Greek salad and Lemon egg soup. We had curry and Biryani for dinner. The Naan is excellent!
Great Indian food.   Great service.
The food is authentic and fresh. It is Beautiful inside!!
The food is great, and the atmosphere is quaint. Will be back.
It's okay

I fell head over heels in love with Indian cuisine because of this restaurant!  I was told that the Chicken Tikka Masala was the most popular Indian dish in both the United Kingdom and the United States, so of course, that's the dish I tried the first time I was there. I was not in the least disappointed. I ordered naan to go with it and liked that so much I ordered another. I shamefully ate ALL of it with no regrets whatsoever. Since then, I have enjoyed the Lamb Korma, the Mali Kofta, and the Shrimp Mykelly, just to name a few. On this most recent visit, I ventured to the Chicken Biryani and found yet another new favorite! I have never once been upset that I ordered one dish and not another as they are all absolutely distinct yet equally AMAZING! Their speciality cocktails are top notch and I love the simple yet inclusive wine offerings!

Worst efforts in a resteraunt EVER. Server was the only pleasant part of experience. Order food half hour later told cant have steak salad be another 20 min.  Another half hour got some of food. 1 person food got cold awaiting condiments, 4th person got food as others were done. They didnt charge due these things. But wasted to time for what was recieved. Now at taco bell. At least can receive food
awesome gyros
I had the steak salad.. the service was fantastic.. I will try other dressings.. it felt like a light lunch but I am full..  I recommend this place.

2nd time for supper here.  Previous visit top notch.  This time, not so much.  Didn't have ingredients for our cocktails (mai tai) and I ordered the Indian vegetarian meatballs and got CHICKEN.  Server forgot to ask us for our entree order after our apps and said, "That's why I asked you if you were done with the menus..." The hummus was a very, very small scoop for $7.  The server didn't even KNOW she brought me the wrong order.  I don't think she even looked at the dish.  Did I send it back? No, I ate it and it was tasty but the server was really lost.  Expected better service.

In search for food in midnight in heart of downtown that’s where I found this nice restaurant. Food is tasty, service is amazing, restaurant is new and no trouble to find parking. I recommend this place for food and drinks. Thanks

Worst food I have had in a while. Had the Greek meatballs. The meatballs where dense, and had really no flavor. They reminded me of froze meatballs. The brown sauce was too thick, it also came with rice which was under cooked. My fiance had the lamb gyros asked for no tomatoes. It was loaded with tomatoes and it had way to much sauce. The server was the best part of the experience.

Excellent downtown option for Indian food. Easy to get table between 11-12, before the rush. Lamb korma was great and came with plenty of gravy. Lunch includes both rice and naan--bonus! Will go back.

We have dined there at lunch and dinner.  Very nice clean and cozy atmosphere.  Every item we have tried is excellent.  The variety of dishes is wide from Greek to Indian entrees.  Would easily recommend to anyone who is looking for a nice place to eat.

Vinny’s has become my favorite place to eat in Huntsville!   Some of the fabulous entrées I’ve tried include the Tikka Masala, Mykelly, and Vegetable Biryani with Shrimp. Vinny and his staff are fabulous and very accommodating.  Be sure to try the appetizers and order a slice of cheesecake for dessert!! You won’t be disappointed!  EVERYTHING is delicious! 😋

The food is excellent,  however... Your only drink options are water or alcohol, they don't have an actual beverage menu ( they did provide a wine lost when asked), and the temperature of the restaurant is almost unbearably hot.  I highly recommend getting to go.
Great location in downtown Huntsville. Server was very friendly and the menu had a lot of options. You would be sure to find something you like with the variety of meals on the menu.
Awesome food and service. Prices are extremely reasonable!

As weird as Greek and Indian together sounds, Vinny's is spectacular!! My group had the Chicken Tikka Masala, Chicken Biryani, Lamb Masala, and Chicken Korma all of them were great! The service was excellent, the prices were reasonable, and the facility was nice enough, although the white  with purple lighting was a little much. Overall, I think we found a new favorite Indian place, and got bonus Greek food for free!
Fantastic food and service. Everything we had on the menu was absolutely authentic and made in house. Highly recommend the Korma or the Mykelly.
Delicious!!
The Greek meatballs and lamb kababs were good. Staff were courteous. Restaurant lighting is dim with blue accent lights.
The food is delicious and Tony’s service and cocktails made it even better. This will definitely be a place I’ll go to regularly.

On a whim, our server asked if we would like complimentary tomato soup. I am in no way exaggerating when I say it was the best tomato soup I've ever had in my life, hands down!  The meal was delicious (chili chicken and biryani), the staff was very nice, and the environment was lovely. Not to mention, they have complimentary valet on Friday and Saturday night. I will be returning very soon, and recommend this place in a heartbeat.
I’ve only had the tomato soup and I’m already sold. Nice ambiance. Definitely a hidden gem.

Excellent food and service. Hands down, some of the best food I've had in Huntsville. The Korma was delicious--the perfect balance of coconut, cream, and spices.  The grilled salmon was perfectly cooked, and the sauce was so good, that my friend was tempted to lick the bowl.  We were informed that the owner makes all of the sauces from scratch and to order, and it definitely shows. Our server, Tony, was very friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable. He provided us a wonderful dining experience.  We will be regular customers from now on!
A hidden jewel on the square.  Same location as Papous,  but now an open airy decor with wonderful Greek and Indian food. Fresh strawberries on a delightful cheesecake!
Chicken Biryani was delicious!
Awesome Tikka Masala, we enjoyed the restaurant a lot, everything was great including the service
My family had a delicious lunch here today. The food was excellent and the service was great. We can’t wait to go back!
We had a lovely lunch at Vinny’s today consisting of chicken tikka masala and vegetable biryani. The service was wonderful and we are so excited to have this new restaurant in the downtown!
Amazing place!

We had a wonderful date night at Vinny's! We ordered the samosa and hummus apps. We loved both! We also had the Malai Kofta and the Chicken Biryani. Both were great. We especially enjoyed the biryani with the yogurt sauce. This is a great choice for picky eaters or someone who is new to Indian food. The Malai Kofta was very flavorful and great for dipping the warm pita bread in. We were told the chef prepares his own spices everyday for his curries and sauces. The restaurant was also very clean and modern with fun mood lighting and music. The wait staff were all incredibly helpful and attentive. What a wonderful new restaurant addition to downtown Huntsville!
Very good Indian and Greek cuisine. We really liked the food and the service. Excellent service and nice feel. We are going back for sure.

Thoroughly enjoyed lunch at Vinny's today. We had the spanakopita as an appetizer and this was the best I have ever had. Delicious filo dough and a nice flavorful filling. Tomato based sauce to dip the filo triangles in added nicely to the appetizer. For the main course we had the Chicken Biryani and Chicken Curry. All was nicely home made with good flavors and large portions. We will be back.

I went to the restaurant with my best friend and I have had the best experience yet! From customer service to food quality, Vinny’s exceeded my normal expectations. I had the Chicken 65, Tikka Masala, and their creamy Cheesecake. Everything was literally fantastic! 5 STARS!
Vinny is an excellent cook.  Best Tikka Masala I've ever had and the Indian spiced chicken Wings (I had the Tir style) were amazing.
Very delicious food and excellent service. Vinny came out to say hello to us and offered to explain the differences between each dish and how they were made. Very affordable too.
Fantastic food. Great prices! The hummus is the best I've ever had! I also had chicken briyani. It was delicious!
Really great food and the staff was amazing.
